snippet.textDisplay:
You see, there's a deep philosophical meaning behind the quote: "my stick is better than bacon" Bacon is usually a commonly enjoyed breakfast food, so you might ask how a stick can be better than bacon. You might think "it's just a stick." But that's exactly what they want you to think. Just like the force the stick holds great power not clearly visible to one without knowledge about it. A stick can be used for walking and supporting someone, a stick can be used for self defense if it is strong enough, and a stick can even help with herding animals like....
PIGS
Just like the force the stick is a method that can be used to control and move things. On top of that bacon (or any meat from a pig in general) has been proven to be very unhealthy to the human body and can literally get worms into your brain if not perfectly cooked. You might ask why I mention that. There's something called a jedi mind trick where a a force user can convince someone to believe whatever they say by using the power of the force to mess with their minds. In this situation the stick represents yoda's old age which also shows wisdom which is required for a mind trick. The bacon's "mind meddling" is always negative because it can only harm the one in which the worms are located while the jedi mind trick can be positive depending on how it's used. The last thing I want to conclude with is one final use of the stick. Cooking. In older times people used to put animals on sticks when they cook them. How do they put the animals on the sticks you ask? The pierce the stick right through them which shows how a stick would defeat bacon in any scenario.
